I love the game, its a great package for the price, and the mechanics are excellently crafted. It would be nice to see more variation in map scenarios, however, but this doesn't detract from the game at all.

I am a conosuer of sorts with strategy and tactics games. And this game, well I can only say its brilliant. The complex diplomactic system and nation management is impressive when compared to games like World Conqueror 4. The same cannot be said comparing to 'big boys' like Europa Universalis 4 but theres always bigger competition in the market. Overall great nov done, good game, would recomend. EXCELLENT for the price A lot like HOI4, just on a lower budget - but let that not convince you it's low-value. This is a ~$5 that feels like a $15 game I do wish you could customize the game more though - being able to just have a blank template of the world and put different civilizations where you want would be awesome
